OperationHeadquarters.Description:
Primary structure. Used to receive gathered resources. Capable of deploying all UED structures aside from additional Operation Headquarters.

Enables:
- Salvagers
- Beacons
OperationHeadquarters.Name: Operation Headquarters

Salvager.Description: Basic resource gathering unit for the Directorate army.**Can attack ground units**
Salvager.Name: Salvager

Arsenal.Description:
Provides Logistics Capacity.
Logistics allow you to deploy additional units.
Can be transformed into a variety of defense towers.
Arsenal.Name: Arsenal

MissileTower.Description:
Anti-air defensive structure.

Detector
Can attack air units.
MissileTower.Name: Missile Tower

SuppressionTower.Description:
Anti-ground defensive structure, effective against lightly-armored targets.

Can attack ground units.
SuppressionTower.Name: Suppression Tower

HeavyTower.Description:
Anti-ground defensive structure, effective against armored targets.

Can attack ground units.
HeavyTower.Name: Heavy Tower

InfusionTower.Description:
Support structure. Regenerates health for all nearby allied units.

There is a detection function.
InfusionTower.Name: Infusion Tower

VespenePurificationPlant.Description: Calldown onto a Vespene Geyser to allow harvesting of vespene gas.
VespenePurificationPlant.Name: Vespene Purification Plant

TeleportationNode.Description:
Universal production structure for the Directorate army, capable of deploying any combat units.

Enables:
- Garmrs
- Strike Troopers
TeleportationNode.Name: Teleportation Node

StrikeTrooper.Description:
Highly-trained Directorate infantry.

Can attack ground and air units.
StrikeTrooper.Name: Strike Trooper

PoliticalAdvisor.Description: Master of ideological warfare. Can inspire troops around her to fight harder. It can throw shock and light grenades.**Can attack ground and air units**
PoliticalAdvisor.Name: Political Advisor

Lazarus.Description: Combat medic. Capable of reanimating deceased Directorate infantry UED.**Can attack ground  and air units**
Lazarus.Name: Lazarus

Garmr.Description: Genetically engineered monstrosity. Effective against lightly-armored targets, and it can tunnel through the ground to cross vast distances quickly.**Can attack ground units**
Garmr.Name: Garmr

Taranis.Description: Heavily-armed infantry, effective against clustered targets.**Can attack ground units**
Taranis.Name: Taranis

UEDUnitSpartan.Description: Universal combat robot, effective against aerial targets.**Can attack ground and air targets**
UEDUnitSpartan.Name: Spartan AAC

DrakkarAPC.Description: Infantry armored personnel carrier, from the inside you can attack only ground targets and from a maximum distance of 5. When the Drakkar is destroyed, the soldiers inside do not die and safely leave the car.**Can attack ground targets**
DrakkarAPC.Name: Drakkar APC

Typhoon.Description:
Artillery vehicle. Supports the offensive with devastating missile salvos.

Can attack ground units.
Typhoon.Name: Typhoon LMT

PeenemundeMRLS.Description:
Long-range artillery. Launches missiles that deal devastating damage in the target area.

Can attack ground units.
PeenemundeMRLS.Name: Peenemunde MRLS

Napoleon.Description: Versatile main battle tank, effective against armored targets.**Can attack ground units**
Napoleon.Name: Napoleon MBT

Huracan.Description: Autonomous combat drone. It is extremely effective when storming fortifications.**Can attack ground targets**
Huracan.Name: Huracan

CitadelAAT.Description: Advanced armored unit, equipped with heavy composite armor, powerful primary cannon and a magnetic wave accelerator for an accelerated attack.**Can attack ground units**
CitadelAAT.Name: Citadel AAT

CrimsonEye.Description:
Low-altitude scouting drone.

There is a detection function
CrimsonEye.Name: Crimson Eye

TransportShuttle.Description: Large transport ship, capable of transporting big squads of infantry & armored vehicles.
TransportShuttle.Name: Transport Shuttle

ArsenalHelpDrop.Description:
Provides Logistics Capacity.
Logistics allow you to deploy additional units.
Can be transformed into a variety of defense towers.
ArsenalHelpDrop.Name: Arsenal Help Drop

Valkyrie.Description:
Dedicated AA corvette, capable of eliminating entire squadrons with a single salvo.

Can attack air units.
Valkyrie.Name: Valkyrie

SupportShuttle.Description:
Combat support ship. Can use Cloaking Drone that temporarily cloaks the targeted unit, and is capable of deploying Psionic Suppression Field that prevents any abilities in the area from being cast.

Detector
SupportShuttle.Name: Support Shuttle

Strikefighter.Description:
Armored multirole fighter.

Can attack ground and air units.
Strikefighter.Name: Strikefighter

HonorguardCruiser.Description:
Versatile screening ship.

Can attack ground and air units.
HonorguardCruiser.Name: Honorguard

TacticsAcademy.Description:
Infantry support structure. Provides equipment authorizations and unlocks research projects that enhance all infantry units.

Enables:
- Taranises
- Lazaruses
- Drakkar APCs
- Goliath combat robots
- Defense Towers
TacticsAcademy.Name: Tactics Academy

FieldBureau.Description:
An upgrade structure that supports Political Advisors.

Enables:
- Political Advisors
FieldBureau.Name: Field Bureau

MunitionsFactory.Description:
Vehicle support structure. Provides equipment authorizations for basic vehicles.

Enables:
- Crimson Eyes
- Napoleon MBT
- Typhoon LMT
MunitionsFactory.Name: Munitions Factory

StarshipMaintenancePlant.Description:
Starship support structure. Provides equipment authorizations for basic vessels.

Enables:
- Crimson Eyes
- Strikefighters
- Valkyries
- Transport Shuttles
- Support Shuttles
StarshipMaintenancePlant.Name: Starship Maintenance Plant

MilitaryResearchStation.Description:
Advanced upgrade structure. Unlocks various equipment authorizations for spacecraft & vehicles.

Enables:
- Peenemunde MRLS
- Citadel AAT
MilitaryResearchStation.Name: Military Research Station

TachyonRelay.Description:
Long-range communications array. Provides equipment authorizations for the Directorate Navy assets.

Enables:
- Honorguards
TachyonRelay.Name: Tachyon Relay

EnrichmentTower.Description: Being installed next to mineral druses allows you to extract more minerals.
EnrichmentTower.Name: Enrichment Tower

BeaconUED.Description: UED engineering vehicle. Can be deployed at a specified site in order to calldown Operation Headquarters from orbit.
BeaconUED.Name: UED Beacon
